<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-10-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="305" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.01/21</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chilean Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Mathieu</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-10-09"><hi rend="italic">October 9,
                                1924</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: While it is not the intention of
                            this Government to discontinue dealing with you as Ambassador of Chile,
                            I desire to state in order to avoid misapprehension that it should be
                            understood that this Government’s action in so doing is not to be
                            construed as a recognition of the régime now functioning in Chile as
                            other than the <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> authorities in control of
                            the administration of Chile.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E.
                            Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>